definition: letter/mail/CL:封[feng1]/to trust/to believe/to profess faith in/truthful/confidence/trust/at will/at random

sentences.english: First, we need to enhance high-level exchanges and improve political mutual trust.
sentences.chinese: 一要加強高層交往，增進政治互信。

sentences.english: Mutual information is an important method for multimodal medical image registration.
sentences.chinese: 互信息是多模態醫學圖像配準的一種重要方法。

sentences.english: XXIII. . Both sides stand ready to deepen understanding of each other's development paths and strengthen political trust.
sentences.chinese: 雙方願加深對彼此發展道路的理解，增進政治互信。

sentences.english: The leaders of the two countries visit each other frequently, promoting mutual trust and friendship.
sentences.chinese: 兩國領導人互訪頻繁，相互信任和友誼不斷加深。

sentences.english: You talked about the future of China-Malaysia relationship in your questions. I agree with you that mutual trust comes first and foremost in China-Malaysia relations.
sentences.chinese: 方纔你提到中馬關係的未來，我也以爲首先是互信。

sentences.english: We can build mutual trust through communication.
sentences.chinese: 我們可以透過溝通建立互信。

sentences.english: First, enhancing friendship and political trust and good- neighborliness.
sentences.chinese: 第一，增進睦鄰友好和政治互信。

sentences.english: The experiment results showed that improved mutual information algorithm was feasible.
sentences.chinese: 實驗結果顯示改進的互信息算法是可行的。

sentences.english: Gruevski said that the two countries have shown mutual understanding and trust for each other.
sentences.chinese: 格魯埃夫斯基表示，馬中兩國相互理解，相互信任。

sentences.english: The two countries enjoy frequent high-level exchanges and ever deepening political mutual trust.
sentences.chinese: 兩國高層交往頻繁，政治互信日益加深。

sentences.english: The friendship, service upmost, warm-hearted, mutual trust dedication.
sentences.chinese: 友誼之上，服務爲先，熱心奉獻，互助互信。

sentences.english: The relationship that often develops between a jury and its presiding judge is one of trust.
sentences.chinese: 在陪審團與主持庭審的法官之間經常建立起互信關係。

sentences.english: It is hoped that the Japanese side do more to contribute to China-Japan political and security mutual trust.
sentences.chinese: 希望日方多做有利於增進中日政治安全互信的事情。

sentences.english: In recent years, bilateral exchanges at all levels have increased with friendship and mutual trust enhanced.
sentences.chinese: 近年來，兩國各層次交往增多，友誼和互信增強。

sentences.english: Both sides have shown mutual trust and support for each other and conducted effective cooperation in all areas.
sentences.chinese: 雙方相互信任，相互支持，各領域的合作富有成效。

sentences.english: Kyrgyzstan cherishes the bilateral relations and mutual trust between the two countries.
sentences.chinese: 吉方珍視吉中關係和兩國間的相互信任。

definition: to seek common ground, putting differences aside (idiom)
